# ==========================================================================
# Security headers for karthikonteddu.com  ·  Cloudflare static-assets / Pages
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This file is read by Cloudflare and applied to every response. It adds the
# site's security layer WITHOUT touching index.html, so it is easy to audit
# and instantly revertable (delete this file to roll back).
#
# WHAT EACH LINE DOES (plain English):
#   Content-Security-Policy  the big one. A strict allow-list of where the page
#                            may load code, styles, fonts, images and send data.
#                            Anything not listed is blocked, which neuters most
#                            injection / cross-site-scripting attacks. The list
#                            below is the EXACT set of services the site uses:
#                              · Google Fonts (styles + font files)
#                              · GoatCounter analytics (gc.zgo.at + your subdomain)
#                              · (book covers + app logos are self-hosted in /img,
#                                 so NO external image hosts are allowed here)
#                              · the newsletter form posts to Formspree
#                            'unsafe-inline' is allowed for the inline <style>/<script>
#                            this single-file site relies on; it is an accepted
#                            trade-off because the site renders NO user-supplied
#                            content (nothing an attacker could inject through).
#   X-Content-Type-Options   stops the browser guessing/" sniffing" file types.
#   Referrer-Policy          shares only the origin (not full URL) when leaving.
#   Permissions-Policy       turns OFF camera, mic, geolocation, etc. - unused here.
#   X-Frame-Options + frame-ancestors  forbid embedding the site in an iframe
#                            (anti-clickjacking).
#   Strict-Transport-Security  forces HTTPS for a year (anti-downgrade).
#   Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy isolates the tab from other windows.
#   X-XSS-Protection: 0      disables a legacy, buggy browser filter (modern best
#                            practice is to rely on the CSP above instead).
#
# AFTER DEPLOY: check it worked at https://securityheaders.com (aim for an A).
# If a logo / font / cover ever disappears, a new service was added that is not
# on the allow-list above - add its domain to the matching directive.
# ==========================================================================

/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; base-uri 'self'; object-src 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'; img-src 'self' data: https://karthikonteddu.goatcounter.com https://gc.zgo.at; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://gc.zgo.at; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com; connect-src 'self' https://karthikonteddu.goatcounter.com https://gc.zgo.at; form-action https://formspree.io; manifest-src 'self'; upgrade-insecure-requests
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), camera=(), microphone=(), payment=(), usb=(), interest-cohort=()
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-origin
  X-XSS-Protection: 0
